    <title>18 Rules of Inference in SL</title>
    <link href="http://nichtsein.github.io/2021/09/13/18-rules-of-inference/"/>
    <id>http://nichtsein.github.io/2021/09/13/18-rules-of-inference/</id>
    <published>2021-09-13T13:26:57.000Z</published>
    <updated>2021-09-15T06:08:38.468Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h3 id="Eight-Implication-Rules"><a href="#Eight-Implication-Rules" class="headerlink" title="Eight Implication Rules"></a>Eight Implication Rules</h3><h4 id="The-rightarrow-rules-Modus-Ponens-and-Modus-Tollens"><a href="#The-rightarrow-rules-Modus-Ponens-and-Modus-Tollens" class="headerlink" title="The  $\rightarrow$ rules: Modus Ponens and Modus Tollens"></a>The  <span>$\rightarrow$</span> rules: Modus Ponens and Modus Tollens</h4><p>MP: </p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}x→y,  x : y\end{align*}</script><p>MT: </p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}x→y, \neg y: \neg x\end{align*}</script><a id="more"></a><p>&emsp;</p><h4 id="The-wedge-rules-Conjunction-and-Simplification"><a href="#The-wedge-rules-Conjunction-and-Simplification" class="headerlink" title="The $\wedge$ rules: Conjunction and Simplification"></a>The $\wedge$ rules: Conjunction and Simplification</h4><p>Conj: </p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}x, y : x \wedge y\end{align*}</script><p>Simp: </p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}x \wedge  y: x\\x \wedge y: y\end{align*}</script><p>&emsp;</p><h4 id="The-vee-rules-Addition-and-Disjunctive-Syllogism"><a href="#The-vee-rules-Addition-and-Disjunctive-Syllogism" class="headerlink" title="The $\vee$ rules: Addition and Disjunctive Syllogism"></a>The $\vee$ rules: Addition and Disjunctive Syllogism</h4><p>Add: </p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}x : x \vee y\end{align*}</script><p>DS: </p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}x \vee y , \neg x : y\\x \vee y , \neg y : x\end{align*}</script><p> &emsp;</p><h4 id="The-double-rightarrow-rules-Hypothetical-Syllogism-and-Constructive-Dilemma"><a href="#The-double-rightarrow-rules-Hypothetical-Syllogism-and-Constructive-Dilemma" class="headerlink" title="The double $\rightarrow$ rules: Hypothetical Syllogism and Constructive Dilemma"></a>The double $\rightarrow$ rules: Hypothetical Syllogism and Constructive Dilemma</h4><p>HS: </p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}x→y, y→z : x→z\end{align*}</script><p>CD: </p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}w \vee x, w→y, x→z : y \vee z\end{align*}</script><h3 id="Ten-Valid-Equivalences"><a href="#Ten-Valid-Equivalences" class="headerlink" title="Ten Valid Equivalences"></a>Ten Valid Equivalences</h3><p><strong>The double-colon symbol <strong style="color:red;">::</strong></strong>, when placed between two statements, this symbol means that the two statements are equivalent — that is, you can substitute one for the other whenever needed.</p><h4 id="Double-Negation-DN"><a href="#Double-Negation-DN" class="headerlink" title="Double Negation (DN)"></a>Double Negation (<strong>DN</strong>)</h4><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}x ::  \neg \neg x\end{align*}</script><h4 id="Contraposition-Contra"><a href="#Contraposition-Contra" class="headerlink" title="Contraposition (Contra)"></a>Contraposition (<strong>Contra</strong>)</h4><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}x \rightarrow y :: \neg y \rightarrow \neg x\end{align*}</script><h4 id="Implication-Impl"><a href="#Implication-Impl" class="headerlink" title="Implication (Impl)"></a>Implication (<strong>Impl</strong>)</h4><p>When you know that the statement x → y is true, you know that either x is false (that is, $\neg x$ is true) or that y is true. In other words, you know that the statement $\neg  x \vee y$ is true.</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}x \rightarrow y :: \neg x \vee y\end{align*}</script><div class="table-container"><table><thead><tr><th style="text-align:center">x</th><th style="text-align:center">y</th><th style="text-align:center">$x \rightarrow y$</th><th style="text-align:center">$\neg x \vee y$</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td style="text-align:center"><strong>T</strong></td><td style="text-align:center"><strong>T</strong></td><td style="text-align:center"><strong>T</strong></td><td style="text-align:center"><strong>T</strong></td></tr><tr><td style="text-align:center">T</td><td style="text-align:center">F</td><td style="text-align:center">F</td><td style="text-align:center">F</td></tr><tr><td style="text-align:center"><strong>F</strong></td><td style="text-align:center"><strong>T</strong></td><td style="text-align:center"><strong>T</strong></td><td style="text-align:center"><strong>T</strong></td></tr><tr><td style="text-align:center"><strong>F</strong></td><td style="text-align:center"><strong>F</strong></td><td style="text-align:center"><strong>T</strong></td><td style="text-align:center"><strong>T</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Example: </p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}P \rightarrow Q, P \vee R: Q \vee R\end{align*}</script><p>Proof:</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}&1 \quad P \rightarrow Q \tag P\\&2 \quad P \vee R \tag P\\&3 \quad \neg P \vee Q  \tag{1 Impl}\\&4 \quad \neg Q \rightarrow \neg P \tag{1 Contra}\\&5 \quad \neg P \rightarrow R \tag{2 Impl}\\&6 \quad \neg R \rightarrow P \tag{2 Contra}\\&7 \quad \neg Q \rightarrow R \tag{4,5 HS}\\&8 \quad Q \vee R \tag{7 Impl}\end{align*}</script><h4 id="Exportation-Exp"><a href="#Exportation-Exp" class="headerlink" title="Exportation (Exp)"></a>Exportation (Exp)</h4><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}x\rightarrow (y\rightarrow z)::(x\wedge y)\rightarrow z\end{align*}</script><p>Example:</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">(P\wedge Q)\rightarrow R,\neg R \vee S,P:Q \rightarrow S</script><p>Proof:</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}&1 \quad  (P\wedge Q)\rightarrow R \tag P\\&2 \quad  \neg R \vee S \tag P\\&3 \quad  p  \tag{1 Impl}\\&4 \quad  P \rightarrow (Q \rightarrow R) \tag{1 Exp}\\&5\quad  Q \rightarrow R \tag{3,4 MP}\\&6\quad  R \rightarrow S \tag{2  Impl}\\&7\quad  Q \rightarrow S \tag{5,6 HS}\end{align*}</script><h4 id="Commutation-Comm"><a href="#Commutation-Comm" class="headerlink" title="Commutation (Comm)"></a>Commutation (Comm)</h4><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}x \wedge y ::y \wedge x\\x \vee y::y \vee x\end{align*}</script><p>Example:</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}P \wedge ( \neg Q \rightarrow R):(R \vee Q) \wedge P\end{align*}</script><p>Proof:</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}&1 \quad  P \wedge ( \neg Q \rightarrow R) \tag P\\&2 \quad  P \tag {1 Simp}\\&3 \quad  \neg Q \rightarrow R  \tag{1 Simp}\\&4 \quad  Q \vee R \tag{3 Impl}\\&5\quad  R \vee Q \tag{4 Comm}\\&6\quad  (R \vee Q ) \wedge P \tag{5 Conj}\end{align*}</script><p>&emsp;</p><h4 id="Association-Assoc"><a href="#Association-Assoc" class="headerlink" title="Association (Assoc)"></a>Association (Assoc)</h4><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}(x \wedge y ) \wedge z:: x \wedge ( y\wedge z)\\(x \vee y )\vee z:: x \vee ( y\vee z)\end{align*}</script><p>Example:</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}(P \rightarrow Q) \vee R : Q\vee (R \vee \neg P)\end{align*}</script><p>Proof:</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}&1 \quad  (P \rightarrow Q)  \tag P\\&2 \quad  ( \neg  P \vee Q) \vee R  \tag { 1 Impl }\\&3 \quad (Q \vee \neg P) \vee R   \tag{ 2 Comm }\\&4 \quad  Q \vee ( \neg P \vee R)  \tag{ 3 Assoc }\\&5\quad Q \vee (R \vee \neg  P)  \tag{ 4 Comm }\end{align*}</script><p>&emsp;</p><h4 id="Distribution-Dist"><a href="#Distribution-Dist" class="headerlink" title="Distribution (Dist)"></a>Distribution (Dist)</h4><p>I have a pet <strong><em>and</em></strong> it’s <strong><em>either</em></strong> a cat <strong><em>or</em></strong> a dog.          $x \wedge ( y \vee z)$</p><p><strong><em>Either</em></strong> I have a pet <strong><em>and</em></strong> it’s a cat <strong><em>or</em></strong> I have a pet <strong><em>and</em></strong> it’s a dog.           $(x \wedge y) \vee( x \wedge z)$</p><p>I have to take <strong><em>either</em></strong> organic chemistry <strong><em>or both</em></strong> botany <strong><em>and</em></strong> zoology.                 $x \vee ( y \wedge z)$</p><p>I have to take <strong><em>either</em></strong> organic chemistry <strong><em>or</em></strong> botany, <strong><em>and</em></strong> I also have to take either organic chemistry <strong><em>or</em></strong> zoology.              $(x \vee y) \wedge( x \vee z)$</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}x \wedge ( y \vee z) :: (x \wedge y) \vee( x \wedge z)\\x \vee ( y \wedge z) :: (x \vee y) \wedge( x \vee z)\end{align*}</script><p>&emsp;</p><p>Example:</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}Q \vee R, \neg ( P \wedge Q), P: R\end{align*}</script><p>Proof:</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}&1 \quad  Q \vee R  \tag P\\&2 \quad  \neg ( P \wedge Q)  \tag { P }\\&3 \quad   P \tag{ P }\\&4 \quad  P \wedge (Q \vee R )  \tag{ 1,3 Conj }\\&5\quad (P \wedge Q)\vee ( P \wedge R)   \tag{  4 Dist }\\&6\quad  P \wedge R  \tag{ 2,5 DS }\\&7\quad  R  \tag{6 Simp}\end{align*}</script><h4 id="DeMorgan’s-Theorem-DeM"><a href="#DeMorgan’s-Theorem-DeM" class="headerlink" title="DeMorgan’s Theorem (DeM)"></a>DeMorgan’s Theorem (DeM)</h4><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}\neg (x\wedge y) :: \neg x \vee \neg y\\\neg (x\vee y) :: \neg x \wedge \neg y\end{align*}</script><p>&emsp;</p><p>It’s <strong><em>not true</em></strong> that I’m <strong><em>both</em></strong> rich <strong><em>and</em></strong> famous.     $\neg (x\wedge y)$</p><p><strong><em>Either</em></strong> I’m <strong><em>not</em></strong> rich <strong><em>or</em></strong> I’m <strong><em>not</em></strong> famous.     $\neg x \vee \neg y$</p><p>Jack is <strong><em>neither</em></strong> a doctor <strong><em>nor</em></strong> a lawyer.      $\neg (x\vee y) $</p><p> Jack <strong><em>isn’t</em></strong> a doctor and he <strong><em>isn’t</em></strong> a lawyer.      $\neg x \wedge \neg y$</p><p>&emsp;</p><p>Example:</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}Q \vee R, \neg (P\wedge Q), P:R\end{align*}</script><p>Proof:</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}&1 \quad  Q \vee R  \tag p\\&2 \quad  \neg (P\wedge Q)  \tag { p }\\&3 \quad  P  \tag{ p }\\&4 \quad \neg P \vee \neg Q   \tag{2 DeM  }\\&5\quad  \neg Q \tag{3,4 DS}\\&6\quad R   \tag{ 1,5 DS }\end{align*}</script><h4 id="Tautology-Taut"><a href="#Tautology-Taut" class="headerlink" title="Tautology (Taut)"></a>Tautology (Taut)</h4><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}x\wedge x ::x\\x \vee x::x\end{align*}</script><p>Example:</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}P \rightarrow \neg P: \neg P\end{align*}</script><p>Proof:</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}&1 \quad P \rightarrow \neg  P  \tag P\\&2 \quad  \neg P \vee \neg P  \tag {1 Impl }\\&3 \quad  \neg P  \tag{ 2 Taut }\end{align*}</script><h4 id="Equivalence-Equiv"><a href="#Equivalence-Equiv" class="headerlink" title="Equivalence (Equiv)"></a>Equivalence (Equiv)</h4><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}x \leftrightarrow y &::(x \rightarrow y ) \wedge (y\rightarrow x)\\x \leftrightarrow y &::(x\wedge y)\vee ( \neg x \wedge \neg y)\end{align*}</script><p>Example 1:</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}P \leftrightarrow  (Q\wedge R), Q: P\vee \neg R\end{align*}</script><p>Proof:</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}&1 \quad P \leftrightarrow  (Q\wedge R)   \tag P\\&2 \quad  Q  \tag { P }\\&3 \quad  (P \rightarrow (Q \wedge R)) \wedge ((Q \wedge R)\rightarrow P)  \tag{ 1 Equiv }\\&4 \quad   (P \wedge (Q \wedge R)) \vee ( \neg P \wedge \neg (Q \wedge R)) \tag{ 1 Equiv }\\&5\quad   P \rightarrow (Q \wedge R) \tag{ 3 Simp }\\&6\quad  (Q \wedge R)\rightarrow P  \tag{ 3 Simp }\\&7 \quad Q \rightarrow ( R\rightarrow P)   \tag {6 Exp}\\&8 \quad  R \rightarrow P  \tag {2,7 MP }\\&9 \quad  \neg R \vee P  \tag{ 8 Impl }\\&10 \quad  P \vee \neg R  \tag{9 Comm  }\end{align*}</script><p>&emsp;</p><p>Example 2:</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}P \leftrightarrow  Q, R\rightarrow (P \vee Q):R\rightarrow (P \wedge Q)\end{align*}</script><p>Proof:</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{align*}&1 \quad  P \leftrightarrow  Q  \tag {P}\\&2 \quad  R\rightarrow (P \vee Q)  \tag { P }\\&3 \quad  (P \rightarrow Q) \wedge (Q \rightarrow P) \tag{ 1 Equiv }\\&4 \quad  (P \wedge Q)  \vee (\neg P \rightarrow \neg Q) \tag{ 1 Equiv }\\&5\quad  P \rightarrow Q \tag{3 Simp}\\&6\quad   Q \rightarrow P \tag{3 Simp  }\\&7 \quad  \neg (P \wedge Q) \rightarrow ( \neg P \wedge \neg Q)  \tag {4 Impl}\\&8 \quad  \neg (\neg P \wedge \neg  Q) \rightarrow (P \wedge Q) \tag { 7 Contra }\\&9 \quad  (P\vee Q) \rightarrow (P \wedge Q) \tag{ 8 DeM }\\&10 \quad  R \rightarrow (P \wedge Q)  \tag{ 2,9 HS }\end{align*}</script>]]></content>
    
    <summary type="html">
    
      &lt;h3 id=&quot;Eight-Implication-Rules&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Eight-Implication-Rules&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Eight Implication Rules&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Eight Implication Rules&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;h4 id=&quot;The-rightarrow-rules-Modus-Ponens-and-Modus-Tollens&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#The-rightarrow-rules-Modus-Ponens-and-Modus-Tollens&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;The  $\rightarrow$ rules: Modus Ponens and Modus Tollens&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;The  &lt;span&gt;$\rightarrow$&lt;/span&gt; rules: Modus Ponens and Modus Tollens&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;MP: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;
\begin{align*}
x→y,  x : y
\end{align*}&lt;/script&gt;&lt;p&gt;MT: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;
\begin{align*}
x→y, \neg y: \neg x
\end{align*}&lt;/script&gt;
    
